00376 DdNode *
00377 Cudd_zddIthVar(
00378   DdManager * dd,
00379   int  i)
00380 {
00381     DdNode *res;
00382     DdNode *zvar;
00383     DdNode *lower;
00384     int j;
00385 
00386     if ((unsigned int) i >= CUDD_MAXINDEX - 1) return(NULL);
00387 
00388     /* The i-th variable function has the following structure:
00389     ** at the level corresponding to index i there is a node whose "then"
00390     ** child points to the universe, and whose "else" child points to zero.
00391     ** Above that level there are nodes with identical children.
00392     */
00393 
00394     /* First we build the node at the level of index i. */
00395     lower = (i < dd->sizeZ - 1) ? dd->univ[dd->permZ[i]+1] : DD_ONE(dd);
00396     do {
00397         dd->reordered = 0;
00398         zvar = cuddUniqueInterZdd(dd, i, lower, DD_ZERO(dd));
00399     } while (dd->reordered == 1);
00400 
00401     if (zvar == NULL)
00402         return(NULL);
00403     cuddRef(zvar);
00404 
00405     /* Now we add the "filler" nodes above the level of index i. */
00406     for (j = dd->permZ[i] - 1; j >= 0; j--) {
00407         do {
00408             dd->reordered = 0;
00409             res = cuddUniqueInterZdd(dd, dd->invpermZ[j], zvar, zvar);
00410         } while (dd->reordered == 1);
00411         if (res == NULL) {
00412             Cudd_RecursiveDerefZdd(dd,zvar);
00413             return(NULL);
00414         }
00415         cuddRef(res);
00416         Cudd_RecursiveDerefZdd(dd,zvar);
00417         zvar = res;
00418     }
00419     cuddDeref(zvar);
00420     return(zvar);
00421 
00422 } /* end of Cudd_zddIthVar */

00447 int
00448 Cudd_zddVarsFromBddVars(
00449   DdManager * dd /* DD manager */,
00450   int  multiplicity /* how many ZDD variables are created for each BDD variable */)
00451 {
00452     int res;
00453     int i, j;
00454     int allnew;
00455     int *permutation;
00456 
00457     if (multiplicity < 1) return(0);
00458     allnew = dd->sizeZ == 0;
00459     if (dd->size * multiplicity > dd->sizeZ) {
00460         res = cuddResizeTableZdd(dd,dd->size * multiplicity - 1);
00461         if (res == 0) return(0);
00462     }
00463     /* Impose the order of the BDD variables to the ZDD variables. */
00464     if (allnew) {
00465         for (i = 0; i < dd->size; i++) {
00466             for (j = 0; j < multiplicity; j++) {
00467                 dd->permZ[i * multiplicity + j] =
00468                     dd->perm[i] * multiplicity + j;
00469                 dd->invpermZ[dd->permZ[i * multiplicity + j]] =
00470                     i * multiplicity + j;
00471             }
00472         }
00473         for (i = 0; i < dd->sizeZ; i++) {
00474             dd->univ[i]->index = dd->invpermZ[i];
00475         }
00476     } else {
00477         permutation = ALLOC(int,dd->sizeZ);
00478         if (permutation == NULL) {
00479             dd->errorCode = CUDD_MEMORY_OUT;
00480             return(0);
00481         }
00482         for (i = 0; i < dd->size; i++) {
00483             for (j = 0; j < multiplicity; j++) {
00484                 permutation[i * multiplicity + j] =
00485                     dd->invperm[i] * multiplicity + j;
00486             }
00487         }
00488         res = Cudd_zddShuffleHeap(dd, permutation);
00489         FREE(permutation);
00490         if (res == 0) return(0);
00491     }
00492     /* Copy and expand the variable group tree if it exists.
00493     ** Create groups for the ZDD variables derived from the same BDD variable.
00494     */
00495     if (dd->treeZ != NULL) {
00496         Cudd_FreeZddTree(dd);
00497     }
00498     if (multiplicity > 1) {
00499         if (dd->tree != NULL) {
00500             dd->treeZ = Mtr_CopyTree(dd->tree, multiplicity);
00501         } else {
00502             dd->treeZ = Mtr_InitGroupTree(0, dd->sizeZ);
00503             dd->treeZ->index = dd->invpermZ[0];
00504         }
00505         if (dd->treeZ == NULL) return(0);
00506         for (i = 0; i < dd->size; i++) {
00507             MtrNode *node;
00508             node = Cudd_MakeZddTreeNode(dd, i * multiplicity, multiplicity,
00509                                         MTR_DEFAULT);
00510             if (node == NULL) return(0);
00511         }
00512     }
00513     return(1);
00514 
00515 } /* end of Cudd_zddVarsFromBddVars */

01376 double
01377 Cudd_ReadUsedSlots(
01378   DdManager * dd)
01379 {
01380     unsigned long used = 0;
01381     int i, j;
01382     int size = dd->size;
01383     DdNodePtr *nodelist;
01384     DdSubtable *subtable;
01385     DdNode *node;
01386 
01387     /* Scan each BDD/ADD subtable. */
01388     for (i = 0; i < size; i++) {
01389         subtable = &(dd->subtables[i]);
01390         nodelist = subtable->nodelist;
01391         for (j = 0; (unsigned) j < subtable->slots; j++) {
01392             node = nodelist[j];
01393             if (node != NULL) {
01394                 used++;
01395             }
01396         }
01397     }
01398 
01399     /* Scan the ZDD subtables. */
01400     size = dd->sizeZ;
01401 
01402     for (i = 0; i < size; i++) {
01403         subtable = &(dd->subtableZ[i]);
01404         nodelist = subtable->nodelist;
01405         for (j = 0; (unsigned) j < subtable->slots; j++) {
01406             node = nodelist[j];
01407             if (node != NULL) {
01408                 used++;
01409             }
01410         }
01411     }
01412 
01413     return((double)used / (double) dd->slots);
01414 
01415 } /* end of Cudd_ReadUsedSlots */

02654                      Cudd_ReadMinHit(dd));

02660                      Cudd_ReadLooseUpTo(dd));

02663                      "Maximum number of variables sifted per reordering: %d\n",
02664                      Cudd_ReadSiftMaxVar(dd));

02671                      Cudd_ReadMaxGrowth(dd));

02674                      Cudd_ReorderingStatus(dd,&autoMethod) ? "yes" : "no");

02807 long
02808 Cudd_ReadPeakNodeCount(
02809   DdManager * dd)
02810 {
02811     long count = 0;
02812 #ifdef __osf__
02813 #pragma pointer_size save
02814 #pragma pointer_size short
02815 #endif
02816     DdNode **scan = dd->memoryList;
02817 
02818     while (scan != NULL) {
02819         count += DD_MEM_CHUNK;
02820         scan = (DdNode **) *scan;
02821     }
02822     return(count);
02823 #ifdef __osf__
02824 #pragma pointer_size restore
02825 #endif
02826 
02827 } /* end of Cudd_ReadPeakNodeCount */

02829 
02844 long
02845 Cudd_ReadNodeCount(
02846   DdManager * dd)
02847 {
02848     long count = dd->keys - dd->dead;
02849     int i;
02850 
02851     /* Count isolated projection functions. Their number is subtracted
02852     ** from the node count because they are not part of the BDDs.
02853     */
02854     for (i=0; i < dd->size; i++) {
02855         if (dd->vars[i]->ref == 1) count--;
02856     }
02857     /* Subtract from the count the unused constants. */
02858     if (DD_ZERO(dd)->ref == 1) count--;
02859     if (DD_PLUS_INFINITY(dd)->ref == 1) count--;
02860     if (DD_MINUS_INFINITY(dd)->ref == 1) count--;
02861 
02862     return(count);
02863 
02864 } /* end of Cudd_ReadNodeCount */
02865

02882   DdManager * dd)

02885 
02886 } /* end of Cudd_zddReadNodeCount */

02903 int
02904 Cudd_AddHook(
02905   DdManager * dd,
02906   int (*f)(DdManager *, void *) ,
02907   Cudd_HookType where)
02908 {
02909     DdHook **hook, *nextHook, *newHook;
02910 
02911     switch (where) {
02912     case CUDD_PRE_GC_HOOK:
02913         hook = &(dd->preGCHook);
02914         break;
02915     case CUDD_POST_GC_HOOK:
02916         hook = &(dd->postGCHook);
02917         break;
02918     case CUDD_PRE_REORDERING_HOOK:
02919         hook = &(dd->preReorderingHook);
02920         break;
02921     case CUDD_POST_REORDERING_HOOK:
02922         hook = &(dd->postReorderingHook);
02923         break;
02924     default:
02925         return(0);
02926     }
02927     /* Scan the list and find whether the function is already there.
02928     ** If so, just return. */
02929     nextHook = *hook;
02930     while (nextHook != NULL) {
02931         if (nextHook->f == f) {
02932             return(2);
02933         }
02934         hook = &(nextHook->next);
02935         nextHook = nextHook->next;
02936     }
02937     /* The function was not in the list. Create a new item and append it
02938     ** to the end of the list. */
02939     newHook = ALLOC(DdHook,1);
02940     if (newHook == NULL) {
02941         dd->errorCode = CUDD_MEMORY_OUT;
02942         return(0);
02943     }
02944     newHook->next = NULL;
02945     newHook->f = f;
02946     *hook = newHook;
02947     return(1);
02948 
02949 } /* end of Cudd_AddHook */
02950 
02951 
02965 int
02966 Cudd_RemoveHook(
02967   DdManager * dd,
02968   int (*f)(DdManager *, void *) ,
02969   Cudd_HookType where)
02970 {
02971     DdHook **hook, *nextHook;
02972 
02973     switch (where) {
02974     case CUDD_PRE_GC_HOOK:
02975         hook = &(dd->preGCHook);
02976         break;
02977     case CUDD_POST_GC_HOOK:
02978         hook = &(dd->postGCHook);
02979         break;
02980     case CUDD_PRE_REORDERING_HOOK:
02981         hook = &(dd->preReorderingHook);
02982         break;
02983     case CUDD_POST_REORDERING_HOOK:
02984         hook = &(dd->postReorderingHook);
02985         break;
02986     default:
02987         return(0);
02988     }
02989     nextHook = *hook;
02990     while (nextHook != NULL) {
02991         if (nextHook->f == f) {
02992             *hook = nextHook->next;
02993             FREE(nextHook);
02994             return(1);
02995         }
02996         hook = &(nextHook->next);
02997         nextHook = nextHook->next;
02998     }
02999 
03000     return(0);
03001 
03002 } /* end of Cudd_RemoveHook */
03003 
03004 
03018 int
03019 Cudd_IsInHook(
03020   DdManager * dd,
03021   int (*f)(DdManager *, void *) ,
03022   Cudd_HookType where)
03023 {
03024     DdHook *hook;
03025 
03026     switch (where) {
03027     case CUDD_PRE_GC_HOOK:
03028         hook = dd->preGCHook;
03029         break;
03030     case CUDD_POST_GC_HOOK:
03031         hook = dd->postGCHook;
03032         break;
03033     case CUDD_PRE_REORDERING_HOOK:
03034         hook = dd->preReorderingHook;
03035         break;
03036     case CUDD_POST_REORDERING_HOOK:
03037         hook = dd->postReorderingHook;
03038         break;
03039     default:
03040         return(0);
03041     }
03042     /* Scan the list and find whether the function is already there. */
03043     while (hook != NULL) {
03044         if (hook->f == f) {
03045             return(1);
03046         }
03047         hook = hook->next;
03048     }
03049     return(0);
03050 
03051 } /* end of Cudd_IsInHook */

03053 
03067 int
03068 Cudd_StdPreReordHook(
03069   DdManager *dd,
03070   void *data)
03071 {
03072     Cudd_ReorderingType method = (Cudd_ReorderingType) data;
03073     int retval;
03074 
03075     retval = fprintf(stdout,"Reordering with ");
03076     if (retval == EOF) return(0);
03077     switch (method) {
03078     case CUDD_REORDER_SIFT_CONVERGE:
03079     case CUDD_REORDER_SYMM_SIFT_CONV:
03080     case CUDD_REORDER_GROUP_SIFT_CONV:
03081     case CUDD_REORDER_WINDOW2_CONV:
03082     case CUDD_REORDER_WINDOW3_CONV:
03083     case CUDD_REORDER_WINDOW4_CONV:
03084     case CUDD_REORDER_LINEAR_CONVERGE:
03085         retval = fprintf(stdout,"converging ");
03086         if (retval == EOF) return(0);
03087         break;
03088     default:
03089         break;
03090     }
03091     switch (method) {
03092     case CUDD_REORDER_RANDOM:
03093     case CUDD_REORDER_RANDOM_PIVOT:
03094         retval = fprintf(stdout,"random");
03095         break;
03096     case CUDD_REORDER_SIFT:
03097     case CUDD_REORDER_SIFT_CONVERGE:
03098         retval = fprintf(stdout,"sifting");
03099         break;
03100     case CUDD_REORDER_SYMM_SIFT:
03101     case CUDD_REORDER_SYMM_SIFT_CONV:
03102         retval = fprintf(stdout,"symmetric sifting");
03103         break;
03104     case CUDD_REORDER_GROUP_SIFT:
03105     case CUDD_REORDER_GROUP_SIFT_CONV:
03106         retval = fprintf(stdout,"group sifting");
03107         break;
03108     case CUDD_REORDER_WINDOW2:
03109     case CUDD_REORDER_WINDOW3:
03110     case CUDD_REORDER_WINDOW4:
03111     case CUDD_REORDER_WINDOW2_CONV:
03112     case CUDD_REORDER_WINDOW3_CONV:
03113     case CUDD_REORDER_WINDOW4_CONV:
03114         retval = fprintf(stdout,"window");
03115         break;
03116     case CUDD_REORDER_ANNEALING:
03117         retval = fprintf(stdout,"annealing");
03118         break;
03119     case CUDD_REORDER_GENETIC:
03120         retval = fprintf(stdout,"genetic");
03121         break;
03122     case CUDD_REORDER_LINEAR:
03123     case CUDD_REORDER_LINEAR_CONVERGE:
03124         retval = fprintf(stdout,"linear sifting");
03125         break;
03126     case CUDD_REORDER_EXACT:
03127         retval = fprintf(stdout,"exact");
03128         break;
03129     default:
03130         return(0);
03131     }
03132     if (retval == EOF) return(0);
03133 
03134     retval = fprintf(stdout,": from %ld to ... ", Cudd_ReadNodeCount(dd));
03135     if (retval == EOF) return(0);
03136     fflush(stdout);
03137     return(1);
03138 
03139 } /* end of Cudd_StdPreReordHook */

03311 static void
03312 fixVarTree(
03313   MtrNode * treenode,
03314   int * perm,
03315   int  size)
03316 {
03317     treenode->index = treenode->low;
03318     treenode->low = ((int) treenode->index < size) ?
03319         perm[treenode->index] : treenode->index;
03320     if (treenode->child != NULL)
03321         fixVarTree(treenode->child, perm, size);
03322     if (treenode->younger != NULL)
03323         fixVarTree(treenode->younger, perm, size);
03324     return;
